  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN132.1-kilavi">tōḻi talaimakaḷai iṭattuyttu <app><lem>vanta</lem><rdg wit="#C7">vantu</rdg></app> talaimakaṉai etirppaṭṭu <app><lem>niṉṟu</lem><rdg wit="#C7">niṉṟucolli</rdg></app> varaivu kaṭāyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">How the confidante sent HER to the place [and then] urged for marriage, 
            confronting HIM who came [back from the meeting].</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="AN132.1">
                <l>ēṉalu miṟaṅkukura liṟuttaṉa nōymalin</l>
                <l>tāykaviṉ ṟolaintaviva ṇutalu nōkki</l>
                <l>yētila moḻiyumiv vūru mātaliṟ</l>
                <l>kaḷiṟṟumukantiṟanta kavu<supplied>ḷu</supplied>ṭaip pakaḻi</l>
                <l>vāṉiṇap pukaviṟ kāṉavar taṅkai</l>
                <l>yampaṇai meṉṟō ḷāyiḻai maḻaikka</l>
                <l>ṇolkiyaṟ koṭicciyai nalkiṉai yāyiṟ</l>
                <l>koṇṭaṉai ceṉmō nuṇpūṇ mārpa</l>
                <l>tuḷitalaik kalaii cāra ṉaḷicuṉaik</l>
                <l>kūmpumukai yaviḻtta kuṟuñciṟaip paṟavai</l>
                <l>vēṅkai viriyiṇa rūtik kāntaṭ</l>
                <l>ṭēṉuṭaik kuvikulait tuñci yāṉai</l>
                <l>yiruṅkavuṭ kaṭāaṅ kaṉavum</l>
                <l>peruṅkal vēlinum muṟaivi ṉūrkkē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>Because the millet has let down [its] bending ears,</l>
                <l>and because, with a look at the forehead of her that has lost [its] choice beauty,</l>
                <l>pain being increasing, this village speaks strange things, (1-3)</l>
                <l>if you have granted [your presence] to the creeper woman of weak nature,</l> 
                <l>rain eyes, choice jewels, [and] pretty, soft bamboo shoulders, (6f.)</l>
                <l>the younger sister of the forest men with bows, so that arrows that break</l>
                <l>the temple, as they rend the face of the elephant bull enter the pure flesh, (4f.)</l>
                <l>take [her and] go, you with a fine-ornamented chest, (8)</l>
                <l>– to the village of your residence with fences of big stones, (14)</l>
                <l>where the short-winged bees that opened the closed buds</l>
                <l>in the vast pools on the slope, having dispersed the drops on [their] tops,</l>
                <l>fill themselves on the broad clusters of the kino tree,</l>
                <l>sleep on the honey-filled heaped bunches of Malabar lilies</l>
                <l>[and] dream of the [musty] ducts in the huge temples of elephants. (9-13)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>
